<grammar>
<section>
<title>Compound words</title>
<sectiontitle>Compound adjectives often use a hyphen (-) between the words.</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>ad_gram3_2_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1></text1>
<text1a>He's &lt;b&gt;kind-hearted&lt;/b&gt;.</text1a>
<sound1>ad_gram3_2_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2></text2>
<text2a>She's &lt;b&gt;strong-willed&lt;/b&gt;.</text2a>
<sound2>ad_gram3_2_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>Compound adjectives often end in &lt;i&gt;-ed&lt;/i&gt; or &lt;i&gt;-ing&lt;/i&gt;.</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>ad_gram3_2_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3></text3>
<text3a>It was a &lt;b&gt;slow-moving&lt;/b&gt; cloud on the horizon.</text3a>
<sound3>ad_gram3_2_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4></text4>
<text4a>It's a &lt;b&gt;rough-edged&lt;/b&gt; diamond.</text4a>
<sound4>ad_gram3_2_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
</grammar>